Company Description


Ubisoft’s 20,000 team members, working across more than 30 countries around the world, are bound by a common mission to enrich players’ lives with original and memorable gaming experiences. Their commitment and talent have brought to life many acclaimed franchises such as Assassin’s Creed, Far Cry, Watch Dogs, Just Dance, Rainbow Six, and many more to come. Ubisoft is an equal opportunity employer that believes diverse backgrounds and perspectives are key to creating worlds where both players and teams can thrive and express themselves. If you are excited about solving game-changing challenges, cutting edge technologies and pushing the boundaries of entertainment, we invite you to join our journey and help us create the unknown.


Job Description


The “Production services” team is responsible for delivering tech solutions and products to support Game Production, Development teams, IT teams, and other key stakeholders for Ubisoft around the world.

The IT Manager's role is to help grow a diverse team of talent, who together form an ecosystem using dev/ops methodologies and frameworks revolving around a CI/CD pipeline and its various components.

You will be responsible for maintaining excellent relations with our business partners and ensuring the solutions are properly delivered across Ubisoft and within its team. You will also closely follow up ongoing projects and validate the timeline, budget all while ensuring deliverables are respected.


Responsibilities



Build an IT roadmap with business partners and under the supervision of the IT Director;

Create an environment built on trust, open communication, creative thinking, and team efforts;

Define &amp; Manage governance to ensure effective communication with internal clients by having regular meetings/steering committee, facilitating prioritization of activities;

Communicate effectively and build a strong relationship with internal clients to understand their reality and constraints, identify needs, provide visibility and strategic counsel, and evaluate alternative business solutions;

Manage a team composed of architects, developers, tech experts, and product managers;

Encourage creativity, calculated risk-taking, and constant evolution and improvement;

Manage project portfolio roadmap and assess risks based on stakeholders’ strategy and the team’s capabilities;

Maintain planning and budget forecasts and communicate with other Managers to ensure appropriate staffing on projects;

Supervise deliverable completeness and quality on projects.




Qualifications



Strong project management and medium sized IT team experience with good knowledge of PMI and/or Scrum methodologies;

Excellent interpersonal skills, displaying effective communication and presentation capabilities;

Working knowledge of developer frameworks and languages as well as the Dev/Ops framework; and CI/CD pipelines;

Working knowledge of an OKR based objectives framework;

Working knowledge of Jira and Confluence;

Knowledge of ITIL practices.




Additional Information


Just a heads up: If you require a work permit, your eligibility may depend on your education and years of relevant work experience, as required by the government.



Skills and competencies show up in different forms and can be based on different experiences, that's why we strongly encourage you to apply even though you may not have all the requirements listed above.





At Ubisoft, you can come as you are. We embrace diversity in all its forms. We’re committed to fostering a work environment that is inclusive and respectful of all differences.

Company Description


Ubisoft’s 20,000 team members, working across more than 30 countries around the world, are bound by a common mission to enrich players’ lives with original and memorable gaming experiences. Their commitment and talent have brought to life many acclaimed franchises such as Assassin’s Creed, Far Cry, Watch Dogs, Just Dance, Rainbow Six, and many more to come. Ubisoft is an equal opportunity employer that believes diverse backgrounds and perspectives are key to creating worlds where both players and teams can thrive and express themselves. If you are excited about solving game-changing challenges, cutting edge technologies and pushing the boundaries of entertainment, we invite you to join our journey and help us create the unknown.


Job Description


The Enterprise Infrastructure team is looking for an IT Operation and Service Manager in Montreal to support their growth as our new colleague. As part of this team, you’ll be joining Ubisoft’s IT and be more specifically responsible for the corporate IT infrastructure and provide services required by all teams at Ubisoft such as networking, storage, directory services, system configuration and deployment tools.

In this role, you will work as both an IT Operation and a Service Manager under a matrix management structure. This means, you will support the World Operation Director and Regional Manager of Enterprise Infrastructure team in overseeing work quality and service level for the team under your management. You’ll also help follow up on and validate the team’s work and coach team members all while bringing your communication, analysis and organization capabilities to the table.


Responsibilities



Lead a global IT service team focusing on Network Security Management all while Managing the capacity resource allocation as per priorities to ensure smooth execution of IT strategy and clean roll out of projects;

Develop KPI and data driven system availability reporting and ensure the monitoring of adherence to high operational standards;

Establish a continuous improvement mindset in the team, define and implement the service improvement plans in an iterative approach;

Fuel automation efforts to reduce manual operations and increase overall efficiency;

Represent the team and service in various global meetings and processes;

Incident Management and vendor cases follow-up as part of Follow-the-Sun supporting efforts – you’ll be the main point of contact regarding feedback about vendor operation;

Provide operational perspectives on the service architecture and design to clients and provide strategic counsel the visibility;

Manage the growth of NCSA Network Management team and the development of its team members;

Focus on creating an environment built on trust, open communication, creativity, and team spirit.




Qualifications



Previous experience of managing technical scopes, whether it’s technical teams or IT project management;

Strong technical acumen on subjects like system administration, networking, automation, orchestration and monitoring;

Expertise in ITIL concepts including ITSM, having in depth knowledge of Agile project managment and the tools supporting these methodologies;

Strong interpersonal and communications skills with the ability to relate technical and non-technical information to different levels of audience written and orally in an international scope;

Strong problem-solving skills and critical thinking skills allowing you to make decisions quickly in an environment where you’ll need to multitask and prioritize.




Additional Information


Just a heads up: If you require a work permit, your eligibility may depend on your education and years of relevant work experience, as required by the government.



